The United Nations Thursday set aside $ 1 million to assess environmental damage caused by this week 's devastating tsunami , as reports of destroyed coral reefs and uprooted mangrove forests began trickling in . 
However , the Food and Agriculture Organization said that massive mangrove planting should be avoided , especially in areas where there are other important ecosystems , such as turtle nesting grounds and sea grass beds . 
A 10-meter high tsunami triggered by a powerful earthquake off northern Sumatra island swept through coastlines across the Indian Ocean on Dec. 26 . 